<br>
In the blanket comments that Abashi and Absor have always told the general public. Monks are the masters of melee damage. Archived and I am sure I can find about a million ways they said it. Meaning no one beats a monk in hands down melee. Period.<br>
<br>
The point is, even with weapons the way they are now, you are still out damaging every other melee class out there besides monks.  How much do you want? A couple more weapons? <br>
<br>
They should be considering fixing a completely bumble fucked high end class, the Necromancers, before they decide to make a couple more weapons for people to loot that got tossed in PVP against a monk.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFF0F5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/uutnayan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Utnayan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Eventempered<br>Retired MMDN Admin</span><br>  Posts: 1084<br> <font color=#D87093>(1/22/02 12:04:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=181.topic&index=102>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: No triple for r00gues!</span><hr size=1> PS: I found this at the safehouse. Take a quick peek at the following, than re-think the ideas on weapons. Pretty much took the words out of my mouth and I didn't have to do any leg work. Just quote. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> &gt; 1) Rogues are doing a few percent less damage than they should really be doing.<br>
<br>
I'm still not convinced about this one. Wendy's parses were with her using a primal sword (13/20) in her offhand, there's about a dozen or so better ratio weapons she could be using that would probably account for those few percentages. In addition, combat in eq seems to have a fairly wide variance, accurately comparing 2 classes DPS to under 10 DPS is a moving target, at best.<br>
<br>
And if we're going to talk about overall DPS throughout all of EQ, you need to factor in DPS rates vs. High Mitigation mobs like some found in Ssra &amp; Acrylia. This one continually is skirted by folks, and I guarantee the 1.0/1.2/1.4 ratio is nowhere close to being maintained for these mobs.<br>
<br>
What's the dmg increase for backstabs by raising 1 point? Is it a linear or geometric progression? What's the damage increase from a 12-13, 13-14, and a 14-15? I've got a feeling this increase is going to be more than &quot;a few percent&quot;.<br>
<br>
<br>
&gt; 2) Rogues don't really have a big selection of weapons. <br>
I agree here that having a large selection of weapons is a good thing, but lets take a look at Post-Sleepers weapon choices...<br>
<br>
Monk<br>
Abashi's Rod (40/30)<br>
Gharn's Rock of Smashing (16/19)<br>
Fist of Nature (15/1<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
Fist of Lightning (15/1<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
Fist of Glowing Acrylia (15/19)<br>
Horns of Chaos (15/1<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
Wurmscale Fistwraps (14/1<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
(The best Ulak so far is 15/20)<br>
<br>
Rogues<br>
Mrylokar's (15/19)<br>
Claw of Lightning (14/1<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
Salindrite Dagger (13/1<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
Braid of Golden Hair (15/21)<br>
Heartwood Thorn (15/21)<br>
Braided Strands of Currupted Mana (12/16)<br>
Serrated Dragon Tooth (13/1<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
Flame Etched Short Sword (12/17)<br>
Dragon Rib Club (12/17)<br>
Kreizerm's Flame (12/17)<br>
Vyemm's Fang (12/17)<br>
Frosted Ice Spike (13/19)<br>
Silver Whip of Rage (13/19)<br>
Dragonspine Rapier (14/21)<br>
Nevederia's Horn (10/15)<br>
<br>
